Director Wang,

5
00:01:52,680 --> 00:01:55,160
is this the bidding document you made?

6
00:01:55,160 --> 00:01:56,330
Yes, it is.

7
00:01:56,330 --> 00:01:58,160
Have you checked it?

8
00:01:58,160 --> 00:02:02,000
President Lu, I received it this morning.

9
00:02:02,000 --> 00:02:04,620
I quickly went through it. I didn't read it carefully.

10
00:02:04,620 --> 00:02:08,010
Now read it carefully.

11
00:02:08,010 --> 00:02:10,700
The 4th line of the 3rd page of the annex.

12
00:02:22,190 --> 00:02:24,170
Sorry, President Lu.

13
00:02:24,170 --> 00:02:28,830
I stayed up too much so I reversed these two groups of numbers.

14
00:02:28,830 --> 00:02:31,660
Also, the 1st line of the 5th page.

15
00:02:35,180 --> 00:02:38,640
President Lu, I left it out.

16
00:02:38,640 --> 00:02:43,450
I just turned to some random pages, and I had already found some mistakes.

17
00:02:43,450 --> 00:02:45,840
Sorry, President Lu.

18
00:02:47,580 --> 00:02:51,290
The depth and quality of the bidding document,

19
00:02:51,290 --> 00:02:55,690
directly relate to the result of the invitation for bids this time.

20
00:02:55,690 --> 00:02:59,180
This also reflects the management of one organization.

21
00:02:59,180 --> 00:03:02,050
The document you made...

22
00:03:02,770 --> 00:03:06,590
is ruining our reputation!

23
00:03:06,590 --> 00:03:10,360
President Lu, sorry. This was also my mistake.

24
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:15,080
We will check and rectify it immediately.

25
00:03:17,290 --> 00:03:19,310
Xiao Liu,

26
00:03:19,310 --> 00:03:23,760
you said "stay up" just now.  Did you blame me for not giving you enough time?

27
00:03:23,760 --> 00:03:28,510
I didn't. The time is enough. It's the problem of my time management.

28
00:03:28,510 --> 00:03:31,210
Now I give you two more weeks' time.

29
00:03:31,210 --> 00:03:33,400
If you still can't make it well,

30
00:03:34,560 --> 00:03:36,580
then I'll give this assignment to someone else.

31
00:03:40,130 --> 00:03:41,680
President Lu!

32
00:03:44,740 --> 00:03:46,720
What's wrong with you?

33
00:03:50,490 --> 00:03:52,390
This is okay. This is okay.

34
00:03:52,390 --> 00:03:55,830
These all work.

35
00:03:56,750 --> 00:03:58,230
- This—
- Old Wu.

36
00:03:58,230 --> 00:04:00,330
One minute.

37
00:04:01,740 --> 00:04:03,580
What's up, Brother?

38
00:04:04,590 --> 00:04:06,850
You see, here...

39
00:04:08,430 --> 00:04:10,070
and here.

40
00:04:10,990 --> 00:04:14,150
And here. What's the problem?

41
00:04:17,090 --> 00:04:19,150
Wei Yayun?

42
00:04:19,150 --> 00:04:20,970
Come here!

43
00:04:25,030 --> 00:04:26,710
Quick!

44
00:04:28,010 --> 00:04:31,670
Tell Mr. Liu... How did you do your work?

45
00:04:32,660 --> 00:04:34,460
You did this?

46
00:04:34,460 --> 00:04:36,510
Yes.

47
00:04:38,720 --> 00:04:41,620
Do you not know common sense?

48
00:04:41,620 --> 00:04:45,020
Here. Compared with the previous document,

49
00:04:45,020 --> 00:04:47,910
it's just rearranged a little. You wrote it like this?

50
00:04:48,950 --> 00:04:50,640
Also here.

51
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:56,790
You don't understand? Or you didn't care?

52
00:04:59,860 --> 00:05:02,450
Mr. Liu, sorry for my negligence.

53
00:05:02,450 --> 00:05:06,910
Because of your negligence, we didn't reach the standard of the document.

54
00:05:06,910 --> 00:05:09,410
You wasted Mr. Liu's time as well.

55
00:05:10,040 --> 00:05:12,850
What are you thinking about all day long?

56
00:05:12,850 --> 00:05:15,270
You want to become a regular staff by working like this?

57
00:05:15,270 --> 00:05:17,370
- I think you should— 
- All right.

58
00:05:17,370 --> 00:05:19,150
Go back to your work.

59
00:05:23,620 --> 00:05:26,870
No young people work hard now.

60
00:05:26,870 --> 00:05:29,450
I thought this part of the job was easy.

61
00:05:29,450 --> 00:05:33,460
I also wanted to give her an opportunity, so I gave the job to her. I didn't expect this.

62
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:37,160
Sorry, Brother. I will change it immediately. Next time, I won't—

63
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:40,510
No need. I will do it by myself.

64
00:05:40,510 --> 00:05:43,200
You don't trust me, do you?

65
00:05:43,200 --> 00:05:47,230
Old Wu, I'm busy here. Let's talk about it later.

66
00:05:47,230 --> 00:05:48,970
Then...

67
00:05:48,970 --> 00:05:51,440
Then let's talk about it later.

68
00:06:04,830 --> 00:06:08,070
When the kids finished lining up after school,

69
00:06:08,070 --> 00:06:10,320
Doudou pushed Miao Miao again.

70
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:12,600
- He almost pushed Miao Miao again. 
 - Really?

71
00:06:12,600 --> 00:06:14,060
He also pushed my William.

72
00:06:14,060 --> 00:06:16,840
Yes, he also teased my Little Xingxing.

73
00:06:16,840 --> 00:06:20,600
Do you think Doudou has ADHD?

74
00:06:20,600 --> 00:06:23,460
Yes. Don't you think that we should call on the school

75
00:06:23,460 --> 00:06:26,680
not to allow a sick kid to stay in the class?

76
00:06:27,930 --> 00:06:30,280
Then, how should we do it?

77
00:06:30,280 --> 00:06:34,360
But is it discrimination if we do it like this?

78
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:37,410
Doudou almost bullied all the kids in the class.

79
00:06:37,410 --> 00:06:41,030
If the parents don't care and the teacher can't manage him well,

80
00:06:41,030 --> 00:06:44,200
then shouldn't we think of a solution by ourselves?

81
00:06:44,200 --> 00:06:47,510
Then, you say how could we call on this?

82
00:06:50,280 --> 00:06:52,810
How about we write a joint letter?

83
00:06:52,810 --> 00:06:54,200
A joint letter?

84
00:06:54,200 --> 00:06:58,000
Yes. Then let's find more parents to sign on the letter.

85
00:06:58,000 --> 00:07:00,490
- This plan works. 
 - Yes, let's do in this way.

86
00:07:00,490 --> 00:07:03,120
Sure.

87
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:04,910
Almost done, right?

88
00:07:04,910 --> 00:07:07,200
Turn on the light.

89
00:07:10,240 --> 00:07:12,410
It's so pretty.

90
00:07:12,410 --> 00:07:15,340
It's beautiful!

91
00:07:15,340 --> 00:07:17,320
- What a happy life the kids are having nowadays.
 - Exactly!

92
00:07:17,320 --> 00:07:20,410
It's all because of an excellent mom like you!

93
00:07:20,410 --> 00:07:24,450
The event looks so nice. Let's hold more like this in the future!

94
00:07:24,450 --> 00:07:26,620
You picked the color very well!

95
00:07:26,620 --> 00:07:32,230
Right, you see. The location is also good.

96
00:07:32,230 --> 00:07:36,150
When it's a party, we need to dress up nicely!

97
00:07:36,150 --> 00:07:39,430
For sure! Let me think.

98
00:07:39,430 --> 00:07:44,080
My husband bought a very beautiful dress for me in Australia awhile ago. I'll wear that one.

99
00:07:44,080 --> 00:07:48,370
I bought a new full-dress last month.

100
00:07:48,370 --> 00:07:52,300
I will put on the antique dress my grandma passed to me.

101
00:07:52,300 --> 00:07:55,140
Antique dress?

102
00:07:55,140 --> 00:07:59,230
- I've never seen that. 
 - Yuwei mom, you can't wear casuals at that time.

103
00:07:59,230 --> 00:08:00,770
I...

104
00:08:00,770 --> 00:08:04,740
Right, Yuwei's mom. You should wear good quality clothes.

105
00:08:04,740 --> 00:08:07,000
Yes. Look at your shoes.

106
00:08:07,000 --> 00:08:10,930
And your bag. You need to change; otherwise, it's too humiliating.

107
00:08:10,930 --> 00:08:14,150
I wear them to work.

108
00:08:14,150 --> 00:08:16,820
Yuwei's mom, come and have some tea.

109
00:08:16,820 --> 00:08:19,690
You have some first. I will finish this.

110
00:08:20,820 --> 00:08:21,980
Thank you.

111
00:08:21,980 --> 00:08:26,270
Which little cat hiding in the blanket?

112
00:08:26,270 --> 00:08:28,830
Let me see?

113
00:08:28,830 --> 00:08:30,180
You came back?

114
00:08:30,180 --> 00:08:31,210
Mom!

115
00:08:31,210 --> 00:08:34,100
- Yes! 
 - Finally, you came back!

116
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:37,370
- What's up? 
 - She disliked my story. We were at odds.

117
00:08:37,370 --> 00:08:40,240
I want to listen to "The Little Mermaid" told by my mom.

118
00:08:40,240 --> 00:08:42,980
- All right 
 - All right. Your mom will tell the story for you!

119
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:44,970
Mom will tell the story for you, okay?

120
00:08:44,970 --> 00:08:46,800
Oh boy.

121
00:08:51,440 --> 00:08:52,990
Here.

122
00:08:54,430 --> 00:08:56,920
I will start now.

123
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:05,800
There were a grandma and six beautiful princesses in the deep of the bottom of the sea.

124
00:09:05,800 --> 00:09:09,620
They don't have legs but only have fish tails.

125
00:09:09,620 --> 00:09:12,630
They are mermaids.

126
00:09:12,630 --> 00:09:15,720
Mermaid princesses are all very beautiful.

127
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:18,780
Especially the youngest one.

128
00:09:25,260 --> 00:09:29,470
Yuwei, I want to ask you something.

129
00:09:30,860 --> 00:09:35,970
Doudou in your class often hits other classmates?

130
00:09:35,970 --> 00:09:41,590
Doudou likes to tease other classmates but he never hits people.

131
00:09:41,590 --> 00:09:44,390
Has he teased you before?

132
00:09:44,390 --> 00:09:50,200
He put the grass of the garden on me today.

133
00:09:52,680 --> 00:09:54,410
What did you do then?

134
00:09:54,410 --> 00:09:57,280
I just left him alone.

135
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:59,580
Did the teacher know this?

136
00:09:59,580 --> 00:10:01,210
Yes, she did.

137
00:10:01,210 --> 00:10:04,680
She criticized him and he apologized to me.

138
00:10:04,680 --> 00:10:08,780
But after a while, he started again.

139
00:10:08,780 --> 00:10:13,070
He went to tease Miao Miao. Miao Miao cried.

140
00:10:13,070 --> 00:10:16,440
Other classmates don't like him, do they?

141
00:10:16,440 --> 00:10:21,590
Sometimes they don't. Sometimes they are okay.

142
00:10:21,590 --> 00:10:22,860
Why?

143
00:10:22,860 --> 00:10:27,660
Because he can imitate little animals. I like to watch him.

144
00:10:30,770 --> 00:10:32,970
18th Century.

145
00:10:32,970 --> 00:10:34,560
Rococo. Watteau.

146
00:10:34,560 --> 00:10:36,700
Bou...

147
00:10:37,310 --> 00:10:40,190
Bou... Bou...

148
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:46,440
Bouchet. Flad.

149
00:10:48,100 --> 00:10:50,960
Bouchet. F...

150
00:10:50,960 --> 00:10:52,690
Bou...

151
00:10:55,540 --> 00:10:57,540
Sixteenth...

152
00:11:03,930 --> 00:11:06,730
The sun rose and the little mermaid

153
00:11:06,730 --> 00:11:09,700
felt light and transparent.

154
00:11:09,700 --> 00:11:13,000
She rose higher and higher riding a rosy cloud.

155
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,860
Higher and higher.

156
00:11:14,860 --> 00:11:18,120
There is one sound from the sky.

157
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:20,000
Zhizhi.

158
00:11:33,200 --> 00:11:36,560
- What's wrong, Mom? 
 - Zhizhi, drink this.

159
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:39,430
- What is this Mom? 
 - This is something good.

160
00:11:39,430 --> 00:11:41,930
Drink it and you can have a son.

161
00:11:43,860 --> 00:11:47,060
Mom, it's a little hot.

162
00:11:47,060 --> 00:11:49,030
Put it there. I'll drink it later.

163
00:11:49,030 --> 00:11:51,070
You have to drink this medicine hot.

164
00:11:51,070 --> 00:11:52,980
It won't be good if it's cold.

165
00:11:52,980 --> 00:11:55,210
- Drink it. 
 - Mom, I'm tired.

166
00:11:55,210 --> 00:11:57,310
Why don't you put it there?

167
00:11:57,310 --> 00:12:01,210
Why aren't you listening to me? I told you, this medicine won't work unless it's hot.

168
00:12:01,210 --> 00:12:03,080
Drink it.

169
00:12:04,450 --> 00:12:06,450
What's wrong?

170
00:12:06,450 --> 00:12:08,570
Mom.

171
00:12:08,570 --> 00:12:11,090
My bad!

172
00:12:11,090 --> 00:12:13,560
What sin have I committed?

173
00:12:13,560 --> 00:12:17,090
I put in a lot of effort to make Zhizhi a bowl of medicine,

174
00:12:17,090 --> 00:12:19,720
but she didn't care at all about my good intentions.

175
00:12:19,720 --> 00:12:23,130
My mom is old. Her health is not good. Why did you fight with her?

176
00:12:23,130 --> 00:12:26,150
Grandma, what's wrong?

177
00:12:26,150 --> 00:12:29,110
Grandma's hand got burned.

178
00:12:29,970 --> 00:12:31,620
Mom, I'm sorry.

179
00:12:31,620 --> 00:12:35,560
- I didn't mean it. 
 - Zhizhi.

180
00:12:35,560 --> 00:12:38,390
Don't think of me as old and troublesome.

181
00:12:38,390 --> 00:12:42,330
I'm doing this for your good.

182
00:12:42,330 --> 00:12:46,170
Don't be mad. I'll drink it next time.

183
00:12:46,170 --> 00:12:49,360
- I'll drink it next time. 
 - Don't wait until next time.

184
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:50,830
- Yang. 
 - Yes, Mom.

185
00:12:50,830 --> 00:12:53,410
There is still medicine in the pot. Hurry and make a bowl

186
00:12:53,410 --> 00:12:56,700
- and drink it while it's hot. 
 - Mom, this—

187
00:12:56,700 --> 00:12:58,600
My hand is fine. Go ahead.

188
00:12:58,600 --> 00:13:00,600
Hurry and go.

189
00:13:02,010 --> 00:13:06,500
Grandma, I will blow for you.

190
00:13:20,030 --> 00:13:23,310
Hurry and drink it. It's not any good cold.

191
00:13:24,320 --> 00:13:27,320
It's late. Don't cause any trouble.

192
00:13:34,700 --> 00:13:36,790
Drink it.

193
00:13:47,860 --> 00:13:49,800
Who is it?

194
00:13:53,290 --> 00:13:58,140
Save me.

195
00:13:58,740 --> 00:14:00,500
Save me.

196
00:14:02,720 --> 00:14:05,780
Gu Xiaoling, you owe us money.

197
00:14:05,780 --> 00:14:07,470
It's time to return it, isn't that so?

198
00:14:07,470 --> 00:14:10,450
When did I owe you money?

199
00:14:10,450 --> 00:14:15,260
Miss Gu, we have your signature on the contract.

200
00:14:15,260 --> 00:14:19,540
You guys are from Chuan Feng Company?

201
00:14:19,540 --> 00:14:21,890
Isn't the payment supposed to be due next month?

202
00:14:21,890 --> 00:14:24,140
The contract says

203
00:14:24,140 --> 00:14:26,280
payment is due every Thursday.

204
00:14:26,280 --> 00:14:28,310
How is that possible?

205
00:14:28,310 --> 00:14:30,330
Look at it yourself.

206
00:14:32,770 --> 00:14:34,690
7th page.

207
00:14:35,470 --> 00:14:39,070
[Party B promises to repay the loan amount of ¥6,000 every Thursday from the beginning of this month, and pay a late fee of ¥600 per day for extension.] 

208
00:14:47,590 --> 00:14:51,970
[Party B promises to repay the loan amount of ¥6,000 every Thursday from the beginning of this month, and pay a late fee of ¥600 per day for extension.] 

209
00:14:52,510 --> 00:14:54,070
Why is it like this?

210
00:14:54,070 --> 00:14:57,220
Okay. It's already Friday.

211
00:14:57,220 --> 00:14:59,840
According to the contract, it's already been 7 days.

212
00:14:59,840 --> 00:15:02,540
You need to pay ¥6,600 now.

213
00:15:02,540 --> 00:15:04,610
You are tricking me.

214
00:15:04,610 --> 00:15:07,370
You are tricking me, wanting me to give you money.

215
00:15:11,450 --> 00:15:13,310
Miss Gu.

216
00:15:16,780 --> 00:15:18,580
Don't be scared.

217
00:15:19,170 --> 00:15:21,690
You ought to know what the consequences are

218
00:15:21,690 --> 00:15:23,660
for borrowing money and not returning it.

219
00:15:23,660 --> 00:15:25,960
What do you guys want?

220
00:15:30,630 --> 00:15:32,810
Hurry and return the money.

221
00:17:47,040 --> 00:17:51,050
Mama, because of you, we get to eat soup dumplings.

222
00:17:52,080 --> 00:17:55,060
Mom waited in line for half an hour this morning to buy these for you.

223
00:17:55,670 --> 00:17:58,110
Thank you, Mom.

224
00:17:58,110 --> 00:18:01,270
Zhizhi, drink this medicine first

225
00:18:01,270 --> 00:18:03,120
and then eat breakfast.

226
00:18:06,620 --> 00:18:10,030
Mom, I can't drink it anymore.

227
00:18:10,030 --> 00:18:11,960
Why not?

228
00:18:12,570 --> 00:18:15,850
I woke up three times last night. I didn't sleep well.

229
00:18:15,850 --> 00:18:18,100
That's right.

230
00:18:18,100 --> 00:18:21,880
Huang Shengshou said that city citizens have poison in their bodies.

231
00:18:21,880 --> 00:18:24,310
This medicine is to help rid your body of these toxins.

232
00:18:24,310 --> 00:18:26,940
Drink it while it's hot.

233
00:18:27,820 --> 00:18:30,600
- Liu Yang—  
 - I have to go to work.

234
00:18:30,600 --> 00:18:35,190
- This early? 
 - Something came up, I have to go in a little earlier.

235
00:18:35,190 --> 00:18:37,160
- Did you finish eating? 
 - Yes, I'm done.

236
00:18:37,160 --> 00:18:39,830
Okay. Then go, don't be late.

237
00:18:39,830 --> 00:18:41,800
Okay, I'll be going now.

238
00:18:42,960 --> 00:18:45,550
Yuwei, be good at school.

239
00:18:49,940 --> 00:18:51,820
Zhizhi.

240
00:18:52,430 --> 00:18:55,560
Here. Drink the medicine while it's hot.

241
00:18:57,180 --> 00:18:59,310
Slowly, it's hot.

242
00:20:05,320 --> 00:20:07,330
Mr. Liu.

243
00:20:08,700 --> 00:20:10,410
Sit.

244
00:20:34,150 --> 00:20:35,850
Here.

245
00:20:36,550 --> 00:20:38,660
Thank you, Mr. Liu.

246
00:20:42,610 --> 00:20:45,010
I was a little rough that day the other day.

247
00:20:45,010 --> 00:20:47,460
Don't mind it.

248
00:20:47,460 --> 00:20:51,410
No, Mr. Liu, you were right to criticize me that day.

249
00:20:53,240 --> 00:20:57,270
Old Wu exaggerated this just to scare you.

250
00:20:57,270 --> 00:21:01,520
Relax. As long as you work hard

251
00:21:01,520 --> 00:21:05,790
and don't make that kind of low-level mistake.

252
00:21:08,880 --> 00:21:11,520
Thank you, Mr. Liu.

253
00:21:12,110 --> 00:21:14,180
Don't cry.

254
00:21:14,180 --> 00:21:16,460
Wipe your tears and eat.

255
00:21:32,680 --> 00:21:35,220
SIster Ziru, over here!

256
00:21:38,760 --> 00:21:42,430
- Why is it only you? Where is Yiming? 
 - He is busy.

257
00:21:42,430 --> 00:21:45,240
Working overtime for Caijin again?

258
00:21:45,240 --> 00:21:47,160
Think so.

259
00:21:50,480 --> 00:21:53,530
Sister Ziru, let me report something to you.

260
00:21:53,530 --> 00:21:56,470
Me and Sister Yuan have officially started to battle.

261
00:21:56,470 --> 00:21:59,450
You finally followed your heart?

262
00:21:59,450 --> 00:22:01,800
I was actually forced.

