00:23:22,270 --> 00:23:25,250
but they don't need cathodal catalysts, either.

290
00:23:25,250 --> 00:23:29,560
We just use a little anodal catalyst.

291
00:23:29,560 --> 00:23:31,770
If the research is successful,

292
00:23:31,770 --> 00:23:34,140
then the current market brands:

293
00:23:34,140 --> 00:23:36,130
Beike, Deke,

294
00:23:36,130 --> 00:23:39,600
and GNB, Lubao,

295
00:23:39,600 --> 00:23:42,360
all of those will die immediately.

296
00:23:42,360 --> 00:23:45,330
He's straight-up slandering Lubao!

297
00:23:45,330 --> 00:23:48,790
If GM Pan came, they'd probably get in a huge fight.

298
00:23:48,790 --> 00:23:51,430
I would honestly love to see that.

299
00:23:51,430 --> 00:23:53,200
That's enough for today.

300
00:23:54,610 --> 00:23:56,640
Professor Gao.

301
00:23:57,920 --> 00:24:00,270
I have a question.

302
00:24:01,450 --> 00:24:05,430
Sure. If the question is too stupid, I'll scold you.

303
00:24:05,430 --> 00:24:09,390
You kept saying that flow cell batteries were walking to their death,

304
00:24:09,390 --> 00:24:11,080
but do you know that

305
00:24:11,080 --> 00:24:15,630
Lubao is going to release a flow cell battery called Lubao 3?

306
00:24:16,890 --> 00:24:19,110
I heard that the Lubao 3

307
00:24:19,110 --> 00:24:22,220
is ranked number one in the market.

308
00:24:22,220 --> 00:24:24,270
We don't have a real hero at the moment, so a chap can become a hero now.

309
00:24:24,270 --> 00:24:28,080
This hero you speak of... Do you mean the membrane-less battery you're researching?

310
00:24:28,080 --> 00:24:31,580
Let me tell you. If my research succeeds,

311
00:24:31,580 --> 00:24:34,880
Pan Zhiyoung's Lubao is going to be forced to kill itself.

312
00:24:34,880 --> 00:24:37,110
So when is your research going to be successful?

313
00:24:37,110 --> 00:24:40,050
When it comes time to be successful, it will be.

314
00:24:40,050 --> 00:24:42,690
Mr. Gao, I have another question.

315
00:24:42,690 --> 00:24:44,620
I feel like I'm playing piano to a herd of cows.

316
00:24:44,620 --> 00:24:47,580
I said I didn't want to come. They wouldn't take no for an answer.

317
00:24:58,850 --> 00:25:04,200
Sister Ziru, are you actually thinking about investing in his project?

318
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:06,350
I am a little interested.

319
00:25:06,350 --> 00:25:08,900
You might as well invest in Lubao instead!

320
00:25:08,900 --> 00:25:11,990
My company is preparing equity financing now.

321
00:25:11,990 --> 00:25:14,580
GM Pan said it himself.

322
00:25:21,530 --> 00:25:25,070
Sister Ziru, something happened with Xiaoling.

323
00:25:25,070 --> 00:25:27,430
- I have to go over. 
 - Do you need help?

324
00:25:27,430 --> 00:25:31,330
- Not now. I'm leaving now. 
 - Hurry and go.

325
00:25:35,780 --> 00:25:37,660
Professor Gao!

326
00:25:38,250 --> 00:25:40,160
Professor Gao!

327
00:25:40,730 --> 00:25:42,740
Professor Gao!

328
00:25:46,240 --> 00:25:50,280
Professor Gao, the objects on the market right now,

329
00:25:50,280 --> 00:25:52,920
are basically all updated versions of old research.

330
00:25:52,920 --> 00:25:54,680
Your research is not like that at all.

331
00:25:54,680 --> 00:25:58,120
Your research can be revolutionary.

332
00:26:05,060 --> 00:26:07,960
I finally met someone who understands.

333
00:26:07,960 --> 00:26:10,880
Can I please take a look at your lab?

334
00:26:13,010 --> 00:26:14,880
You lead me.

335
00:26:55,160 --> 00:27:00,150
Professor Gao, how much more money do you need for your research?

336
00:27:00,150 --> 00:27:04,440
¥20,000,000. If I had ¥20,000,000, I could make breakthroughs.

337
00:27:06,130 --> 00:27:07,930
¥20,000,000...

338
00:27:10,870 --> 00:27:13,190
¥20,000,000 isn't that much.

339
00:27:13,190 --> 00:27:15,380
I can come up with the money.

340
00:27:17,140 --> 00:27:19,250
Okay.

341
00:27:19,250 --> 00:27:21,140
But you have to tell the school.

342
00:27:21,140 --> 00:27:25,060
This donation is made specifically for my lab.

343
00:27:27,510 --> 00:27:30,810
I want to join in the form of investing.

344
00:27:33,150 --> 00:27:34,980
That works, too.

345
00:27:34,980 --> 00:27:39,020
Then you have to also talk with the school.

346
00:27:40,250 --> 00:27:43,330
What if I only want to talk with you?

347
00:27:43,330 --> 00:27:45,630
What does that mean?

348
00:27:47,300 --> 00:27:49,660
I want...

349
00:27:49,660 --> 00:27:52,690
to set up a company for you.

350
00:27:52,690 --> 00:27:55,130
You want me to leave the school?

351
00:27:58,440 --> 00:28:01,940
Professor Gao, with my knowledge,

352
00:28:01,940 --> 00:28:04,790
the school has been cutting your funds for some time now.

353
00:28:04,790 --> 00:28:08,780
There has even been word that some people want to close your lab down altogether.

354
00:28:10,800 --> 00:28:13,460
You seem to know a lot about my situation.

355
00:28:13,930 --> 00:28:16,750
The school has regarded your research as pointless for a while now.

356
00:28:16,750 --> 00:28:18,720
I trust that if the price was right,

357
00:28:18,720 --> 00:28:22,650
they would be willing to give up your research results.

358
00:28:22,650 --> 00:28:24,860
And then...

359
00:28:24,860 --> 00:28:27,560
And then you can work in your very own lab

360
00:28:27,560 --> 00:28:29,530
with no limits.

361
00:28:29,530 --> 00:28:32,340
You never have to worry about funds ever again.

362
00:28:32,340 --> 00:28:34,910
There's definitely a catch.

363
00:28:35,820 --> 00:28:39,270
I just want to have some shares within your company.

364
00:28:40,320 --> 00:28:43,690
- How much? 
 - 60%

365
00:28:47,990 --> 00:28:50,470
¥20,000,000?

366
00:28:50,470 --> 00:28:54,420
For ¥20,000,000, you want 60% of my shares?

367
00:28:59,030 --> 00:29:01,170
Professor Gao,

368
00:29:01,690 --> 00:29:05,280
usually, angel-like investments don't go past 30%,

369
00:29:05,280 --> 00:29:09,920
and they even require that in five years, they get five times the amount in return.

370
00:29:10,410 --> 00:29:12,930
But in my current state, that's impossible.

371
00:29:12,930 --> 00:29:14,630
Yeah.

372
00:29:14,630 --> 00:29:18,600
You can't even guarantee that you'll have a breakthrough with ¥20,000,000, can you?

373
00:29:22,560 --> 00:29:27,480
Professor Gao, the industry trusts your research even less.

374
00:29:27,480 --> 00:29:31,880
More than 50% of people think you are poles apart.

375
00:29:31,880 --> 00:29:33,950
Over 90% of people,

376
00:29:33,950 --> 00:29:36,210
think that you cannot be successful.

377
00:29:36,210 --> 00:29:39,040
The most trusted science magazine predicts that

378
00:29:39,040 --> 00:29:42,580
if membrane-less batteries want to successfully enter the market,

379
00:29:42,580 --> 00:29:45,400
then there still needs to be 20 years.

380
00:29:57,150 --> 00:30:00,720
Then, why are you looking for me?

381
00:30:00,720 --> 00:30:02,660
I am an investor.

382
00:30:02,660 --> 00:30:06,450
I understand the risks much differently than other people do.

383
00:30:07,060 --> 00:30:09,980
I won't accept 60%.

384
00:30:12,050 --> 00:30:15,130
60% does seem high.

385
00:30:15,130 --> 00:30:16,840
But don't forget.

386
00:30:16,840 --> 00:30:20,690
I am putting myself at a 99% risk.

387
00:30:23,440 --> 00:30:25,200
You can leave now.

388
00:30:28,970 --> 00:30:32,000
Professor Gao, I'm telling you.

389
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:34,340
I trust that not a single person

390
00:30:34,340 --> 00:30:36,820
will take this much money and time

391
00:30:36,820 --> 00:30:42,330
- to invest in a project that has a 99% chance to fail. 
 - I need to go to work now!

392
00:30:44,230 --> 00:30:46,000
Work.

393
00:30:50,930 --> 00:30:52,550
Okay.

394
00:30:52,550 --> 00:30:55,060
This is my business card.

395
00:30:55,060 --> 00:30:58,010
If you change your mind, please contact me.

396
00:31:01,960 --> 00:31:04,320
I'll put it here.

397
00:31:05,140 --> 00:31:06,930
I'll leave.

398
00:31:10,870 --> 00:31:13,020
[Wang Ziru] 
 [Chief Executive Officer]

